      "value": "<p><b>Source</b> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 43</em>, <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 137</em></p>\n<h3>Statistics</h3><p><b>Damage</b> 1d4 (small), 1d6 (medium); <b>Critical</b> x4; <b>Range</b> 10 ft.; <b>Type</b> P</p>\n<p><b>Misfire</b> 1-4 (5 ft.); <b>Capacity</b> 1</p>\n<h3>Description</h3>\n<p>This primitive firearm is merely a long tube that, when ignited, propels forth a short gout of flame and a javelin. Unlike other firearms, the fire lance is wildly imprecise, and targets AC rather than touch AC. A fire lance is always treated as having the broken condition for the purpose of determining the effects of a misfire. A fire lance uses a javelin and 2 doses of black powder as ammunition.</p>"
